        "id": "3c807d00c3c2a045",
        "text": "So, how do we control the flow out (drawdown) of carbon from the atmosphere safely? Well, nature’s key to this is plants and photosynthesis. Plants are brilliant. They take in CO2, give us oxygen to breathe, and store the carbon in their body. As parts break away (eg leaves in autumn), they decompose and create stable soil carbon. Over time, layers build up pressure, compressing carbon and creating fossil fuels: Nature’s safe storage for carbon…and note, renewable, over long time-frames. The issue is that we have been digging them up, and burning them, and releasing the carbon into the atmosphere."
