      "id": "e8d4469e82dc30b6",
      "item": {
        "type": "markdown",
        "id": "e8d4469e82dc30b6",
        "text": "If we do not understand the systems around us, we only have one option and that is to react. Sometimes our reactions only serve to compound the problem we’re already reacting to: We see ourselves as victims of something or someone we cannot influence. If the same problem persists or repeats we may start to notice a pattern and we adapt our behavior to protect ourselves from the phenomenon. We still see the problem as outside ourselves and outside our influence. If instead, we start to think about the system of cause and effect relationships and the feedback creating the problem, we start to understand our relationship to the problem and our power to fix it. This can be a profound and truly life changing experience."
